VulcanForms

Founded in 2015 by Martin C. Feldmann and Professor John Hart of MIT, VulcanForms invented and commercialized the world’s first industrially scalable laser metal additive manufacturing solution and operates integrated digital production systems. 

By combining advanced additive and subtractive technologies merged through a digital thread, VulcanForms captures the full value chain for precision engineered metal components and assemblies.  VulcanForms is delivering a full-stack U.S.-based digital manufacturing solution with unprecedented speed, precision, quality, and scale. 

VulcanForms believes that the United States faces a historically significant need — and opportunity — to re-establish an innovative manufacturing ecosystem. VulcanForms’ groundbreaking technologies coupled with world-class engineering and operations expertise are accelerating innovation for leading medical, defense, aerospace, and semiconductor companies.
